data.content:
**No Thread.Abort migration is needed here.**

Your code uses only `Thread.Start`, `Thread.Join`, and `Thread.Sleep` — none of which involve `Thread.Abort`, `ThreadAbortException`, `Thread.ResetAbort`, or `Thread.Interrupt`. These APIs work identically in modern .NET and will compile and run correctly on .NET 8 as-is.

---

**Optional modernization** (unrelated to Thread.Abort migration):

You could simplify this with `Parallel.ForEach` or `Task.Run`, which handles thread pooling and is more idiomatic in .NET 8:

```csharp
public void RunBatch(List<WorkItem> items)
{
    Parallel.ForEach(items, item =>
    {
        Thread.Sleep(100);
        item.Result = ComputeResult(item.Input);
    });
}
```

But again — this is purely optional. Your existing code requires zero changes for the .NET 8 migration with respect to thread termination APIs.
